subject: p17337033
History: History: M with DM1 who is presenting with elevations of blood sugar, vomiting and abdominal pain.
Findings: Heart size is normal. The aorta is tortuous. Unchanged widening of the mediastinum attributable to mediastinal lipomatosis is re-demonstrated. Hilar contours are unremarkable. Pulmonary vasculature is not engorged. Lungs are clear. No pleural effusion, focal consolidation or pneumothorax is demonstrated. There are no acute osseous abnormalities.
